############## SETUP TOMCAT

*create new instance

*"sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel" (to install java)
*" java -version"

DOWNLOAD & INSTALL TOMCAT

*pwd  we are in /home/ec2-user to change /opt/

*cd /opt/ (do not install in /home/ec2-user because instance will delect all gone && so recommened path for setup software, like we have cd /var/,ect... )

* google search https://tomcat.apache.org/download-90.cgi

* double click on "tar.gz (pgp, sha512)" & copy link

*"sudo wget <paste the copy link>"

*"sudo tar xf apache-tomcat-9.0.71.tar.gz"

*"sudo mv apache-tomcat-9.0.71 tomcat9"

*"ls -ltr" (change premisions on tomcat floder root:root to ec2-user:ec2-user)

*"sudo chown -R ec2-user:ec2-user tomcat9/"

*"cd tomcat9"

*" ./bin/startup.sh" (copy the public id of tomcat insatnce & search in google id:8080)
 "/opt/tomcat9/bin/startup.sh"

*"./bin/shutdown.sh"
  "/opt/tomcat9/bin/shutdown.sh"
